This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising and enhancement. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions motion blur, which could place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of multiple frames suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
